  "body": "After installing helm from source, if I execute `helm search redis` I get:\n\n```\npanic: runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\n[signal 0xb code=0x1 addr=0x20 pc=0x40dfd0]\n\ngoroutine 1 [running]:\npanic(0x1905e80, 0xc82000e120)\n    /usr/local/go/src/runtime/panic.go:481 +0x3e6\nmain.searchCacheForPattern.func1(0xc8203df680, 0x26, 0x0, 0x0, 0x7f53d2f6f2d0, 0xc8203df800, 0x0, 0x0)\n    /home/migmartri/work/gocode/src/github.com/kubernetes/helm/cmd/helm/search.go:63 +0x40\n```\n\nProblem that seems to be related to the fact that I have not initialized helm yet.\n\nSo executing `helm init` fixed the issue.\n\n```\n$ helm search redis\nkubernetes-charts/redis-2.0.0.tgz\n```\n\nI have noticed that for some other commands there is a guard statement that tells you that the file does not exist, for example:\n\n```\n$helm fetch foo\nError: open /home/migmartri/.helm/repository/repositories.yaml: no such file or directory\n```\n\nWe might want to implement the same approach for the search command. Ideally with a message a little bit more actionable that says something about executing helm init first (although this could be moved to another issue)\n\nWhat do you think?\n",
